comments: Gay (SAS) legally contests House Jr.'s (HOU) shot near the rim.
Oladipo (HOU) and White (SAS) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
Tucker (HOU) makes contact with DeRozan's (SAS) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Tucker (HOU) and DeRozan (SAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
DeRozan (SAS) draws House Jr. (HOU) into the air towards him and the contact results in a foul on House Jr. even if contact is initiated by DeRozan.
Mills (SAS) is moving alongside Wall's (HOU) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive.
Gay (SAS) and Wall (HOU) make incidental contact with one another as Wall is passing the ball.
Tucker (HOU) legally contests DeRozan's (SAS) jump shot attempt.

As Wall (HOU) is making a natural basketball move, his arm brushes the side of Mills' (SAS) head/face.   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Mills (SAS) has an arm extended in Wall's (HOU) path but the contact is marginal and Wall moves through it.
White (SAS) maintains verticality as he defends Wall's (HOU) driving shot attempt.
Oladipo (HOU) commits a take foul on Mills (SAS).
Gay (SAS) dislodges Tucker (HOU) from his legally obtained screening position.
House Jr. (HOU) commits a take foul on Gay (SAS).
Mills (SAS) and Wall (HOU) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
